

Use this exact file name if your repo expects uppercase, but in practice Docker usually expects `Dockerfile`. Since you asked for `DOCKERFILE`, I’m giving content; save as requested.

```dockerfile
FROM python:3.11-slim

WORKDIR /app

COPY deploy /app/deploy
COPY quantized /app/quantized
COPY README.md /app/README.md

RUN pip install --no-cache-dir fastapi uvicorn pydantic

EXPOSE 8000

CMD ["uvicorn", "deploy.app:app", "--host", "0.0.0.0", "--port", "8000"]